race.comment: HERAULT (9) won a Lark Hill trial easily and resumed much improved when narrowly beaten here over shorter. It was a tough effort suggesting there's more to come. The longer sprint should hold no fears and he can go one better. ADMIRE ASTRA (13) was heavily bet the same day on debut and went close over 1300m. She also has plenty of scope for improvement and Pike sticking aboard is a plus. Unlike the above pair BUON AMICI (8) maps for a soft run and has needed the two runs this preparation. Pike gets off but he rates well at best and has to be considered. GINGER AND TONIC (7) resumes and missed a nose in a recent Lark Hill trial. Has placed fresh and has been unlucky not the have broken through. Worth including at a price.
